comment_message:
@Lee Kee Seng: Are you serious? o_O people are complaining that they can't get a apartment from HDB!!!!! We need to construct more HDBs and basic infrastructure to sustain the current demands.

@Azhar Khamis: the situation in Australia and other countries are not as rosy as they sound like. yes. they maybe blue collar workers. getting high salaries. but overall development of their country is low and the inflation in labour generated. Is there something wrong if the pay for macdonalds clerk is AUS 18? We pay low wage construction workers as per what the market is affording? If you don't mind paying more for your HDB flats or private housing by increasing local wage component and getting locals to build, it is ok. but it will bring another set of problems like competitiveness from Singapore (human capital).  

Samster: Please lah... some proof please. you think it is so easy to control inflation? by increasing the Sing dollar, it has reduced some of the inflationary pressure. I think you need some binoculars to look further than SG to see what is it really like for other countries. talk is cheap.

@jefferson: why did we have to open our doors to low wage blue collar foreigners at the first place? have you thought of that? if it was you cleaning the toilets, building the houses, cleaning the tables and etc. how much would you think your salary would increase? in reality, all parents want their kids to excel and get a good job. you mean by throwing carrots like SDP proposed changes/ plans?
